This release has minor content improvements, including the addition of a new class Sertoli cell barrier for GO.

We have switched to using [ROBOT](https://github.com/ontodev/robot/)
for releases. This eliminates some of the redundancy previously seen
in the basic OBO graph.

Overton, J. A., Dietze, H., Essaid, S., Osumi-sutherland, D., & Mungall, C. J. (2015). ROBOT : A command-line tool for ontology development. In Proceedings of the International Conference on Biomedical Ontology (ICBO) (pp. 131â€“132). Lisbon, Portugal.

 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) *[has obo namespace](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasOBONamespace)* uberon
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) *[database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)* [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood-testis_barrier](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood-testis_barrier)
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) *[label](http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label)* Sertoli cell barrier
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) *[database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)* MESH:G06.535.166.330.100
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) *[id](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#id)* UBERON:0036185
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) **SubClassOf** [squamous epithelium](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0006914)
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) *[has related synonym](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym)* blood testis barrier { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood-testis_barrier](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood-testis_barrier) } 
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) **SubClassOf** [haemolymphatic fluid-testis barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0014914)
 * [Sertoli cell barrier](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036185) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* The blood-testis barrier (abbreviated as BTB) is a physical barrier between the blood vessels and the seminiferous tubules of the animal testes. The barrier is formed by tight connections between the Sertoli cells, which are sustentacular cells (supporting cells) of the seminiferous tubules, and nourish the spermatogonia. The barrier prevents passage of cytotoxic agents (bodies or substances that are toxic to cells) into the seminiferous tubules. { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood-testis_barrier](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood-testis_barrier) }
